divs: sighting detailsi was cleaning the sensor of my digital camera (nikon d300, 18-135mm lens) and was shooting a frame of clear blue sky to confirm that dirt had been removed. repeated this cleaning action 3 times, after the 3rd time i stepped outside and pointed the camera at clear blue sky and clicked 1 shot off. when i looked at the frame on the camera display i noticed objects in the image that i did not see when i took the photo. i did not see the objects with my sight - did not notice any objects in the sky when i shot the frame. image submitted below. camera: nikon d300 lens: nikon dx 18-135mm exposure: 1\160 sec @ f16 iso 200
Summary: Images showed up unexpected on photo.
